We found a higher risk of liver injury in patients with severe COVID-19 than in those with non-severe disease (OR 2·20 [95% CI 1·60–3·02]; p<0·00001; I
2=36%; figure 6
). Liver damage indices, including ALT, and AST, and total bilirubin concentrations were significantly higher in patients with severe disease than in those with non-severe disease (appendix p 19). However, the pooled analysis did not show a significant difference in albumin concentrations between the two groups (appendix p 19).
